Cloak is a local secrets vault. Secrets are AEAD-encrypted at rest under a key derived from your
passphrase via Argon2id. Reveal is gated behind Touch ID on macOS.

Usage: cloak [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  init           Initialize a new vault (interactive passphrase + KDF autotune)
  add            Add a new secret. Prompts for the value with echo OFF
  set            Update the value of an existing secret. Prompts with echo OFF
  get            Get metadata for a secret (name / kind / tags / timestamps). Never returns
                 plaintext
  list           List secrets (metadata only). Empty vault prints "(no secrets)"
  rm             Remove a secret. Prompts for confirmation unless `--yes`
  show           Reveal a secret's plaintext (Touch ID gated, TTY-only)
  status         Print vault status (path, record count, KDF params, lock state)
  completions    Print shell completions
  daemon-unlock  Push the vault passphrase to the running `cloakd` so MCP peers can serve requests.
                 v0.1 bridge — see the module docs
  help           Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --vault <PATH>
          Path to the vault file (default: `$DATA_DIR/cloak/vault.cloak`)

      --no-biometric
          Disable Touch ID; always fall back to passphrase re-entry on `cloak show`

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
